00:13:16.096 --> 00:13:18.976
Once upon a time in a sunny valley,

00:13:18.848 --> 00:13:22.208
There lived a little lamb named Joshua.

00:13:22.528 --> 00:13:25.920
He was white with black spots, black feet,

00:13:26.048 --> 00:13:27.744
And sad eyes

00:13:28.224 --> 00:13:34.336
Josh felt sad when he saw the other lambs with snow-white wool and no spots.

00:13:34.400 --> 00:13:39.424
He felt sad when he saw the other sheep with their moms and dads.

00:13:39.712 --> 00:13:42.112
Because he didn't have a mom or dad.

00:13:42.976 --> 00:13:48.416
He felt the saddest, however, when he saw the other lambs running and jumping.

00:13:48.288 --> 00:13:49.888
Because he couldn't.

00:13:50.368 --> 00:13:54.048
Josh had been born with one leg that didn't work right.

00:13:54.432 --> 00:13:55.712
He was crippled.

00:13:56.128 --> 00:13:57.920
And he always limped.

00:13:58.080 --> 00:13:59.264
When he walked.

00:14:00.512 --> 00:14:06.464
That's why he always watched while the other lands ran and play.

00:14:06.528 --> 00:14:09.120
Josh felt sad and alone.

00:14:09.152 --> 00:14:12.032
except when abigail was around.

00:14:12.288 --> 00:14:14.848
abigail was josh's best friend.

00:14:14.880 --> 00:14:19.008
She didn't look like a friend for a lamb. She was an old cow.

00:14:19.296 --> 00:14:24.576
She was brown with white blotches that looked like rain puddles on a path.

00:14:24.736 --> 00:14:30.880
Her belly was as round as a barrel, and her voice was always kind and friendly.

00:14:31.008 --> 00:14:34.240
some of josh's favorite hours for spin.

00:14:34.112 --> 00:14:35.520
with Abigail.

00:14:36.032 --> 00:14:40.448
They loved to pretend they were on adventures in distant lands.

00:14:40.512 --> 00:14:45.248
josh liked to listen to abigail tell stories about the stars.

00:14:45.248 --> 00:14:49.312
They would spend hours on the hill looking into the valley.

00:14:49.408 --> 00:14:51.296
they were good friends.

00:14:51.360 --> 00:14:54.176
But even with a friend like Abigail,

00:14:54.048 --> 00:14:56.224
Josh still got sand.

00:14:57.024 --> 00:15:03.424
It made him sad to be the only lamb who could not run and jump and play on the grass.

00:15:03.680 --> 00:15:08.544
That's when Abigail would turn to him and say, "Don't be sad, little Joshua."

00:15:08.800 --> 00:15:11.136
God has a special place.

00:15:11.264 --> 00:15:12.960
For those who feel

00:15:12.736 --> 00:15:13.888
Left out.

00:15:15.328 --> 00:15:18.496
Josh wanted to believe her, but it was hard.

00:15:18.336 --> 00:15:20.992
Some days he just felt alone.

00:15:20.960 --> 00:15:28.352
he really felt alone the day the shepherds decided to take the lambs to the next valley where there was more grass.

00:15:28.448 --> 00:15:31.520
The sheep had been in this valley so long,

00:15:31.232 --> 00:15:33.696
That the ground was nearly bare.

00:15:34.048 --> 00:15:40.192
All the sheep were excited when the shepherd told them that they were going to a new meadow.

00:15:40.896 --> 00:15:46.592
As they prepared to leave, Josh hobbled over and took his place on the edge of the group.

00:15:47.104 --> 00:15:49.536
But the others started laughing at him.

00:15:50.368 --> 00:15:53.760
You're too slow to go all the way to the next valley.

00:15:53.824 --> 00:15:58.336
Go back, slowpoke. we'll never get there if we have to wait on you.

00:15:58.240 --> 00:16:00.096
Go back, Joshua.

00:16:01.024 --> 00:16:05.920
That's when Josh looked up and saw the shepherd standing in front of him.

00:16:06.336 --> 00:16:08.448
There right, my little Joshua.

00:16:08.960 --> 00:16:10.624
You better go back.

00:16:10.528 --> 00:16:12.832
This trip is too long for you.

00:16:12.832 --> 00:16:14.752
Go and spend the night.

00:16:14.560 --> 00:16:15.904
In the stable.

00:16:16.448 --> 00:16:21.184
Josh looked at the man for a long time, and then he turned slowly.

00:16:21.248 --> 00:16:23.296
And began limping away.

00:16:24.320 --> 00:16:27.008
When Josh got to the top of the hill,

00:16:26.976 --> 00:16:32.192
He looked down and saw all the other sheep headed toward the green grass.

00:16:32.256 --> 00:16:35.392
Never before had he felt so left out.

00:16:35.840 --> 00:16:41.472
A big tear slipped out of his eye and rolled down his nose and fell on a rock.

00:16:41.696 --> 00:16:44.576
Then he heard Abigail behind him.

00:16:44.544 --> 00:16:48.832
And Abigail said what she always said when Josh felt sad.

00:16:49.216 --> 00:16:51.872
Don't be so sad, little Joshua.

00:16:52.096 --> 00:16:54.432
God has a special place.

00:16:54.304 --> 00:16:56.384
For those who feel left out.

00:16:56.928 --> 00:17:01.984
Slowly, the two friends turned and walked to the stable together.

00:17:02.880 --> 00:17:08.000
By the time they got to the little barn, the sun was setting like a big orange ball.

00:17:08.160 --> 00:17:13.600
Josh and Abigail went inside and began to eat some hay out of the feed box.

00:17:13.792 --> 00:17:15.616
They were very hungry.

00:17:15.456 --> 00:17:17.536
And the hay tasted good.

00:17:18.016 --> 00:17:22.528
for a little while joshua forgot that he had been left behind.

00:17:22.656 --> 00:17:27.360
"'Go to sleep, little friend,' Abigail said, after they finished eating."

00:17:27.232 --> 00:17:28.960
You've had a hard day.

00:17:29.632 --> 00:17:36.000
Josh was tired, so he lay down in the corner on some straw and closed his eyes.

00:17:35.904 --> 00:17:39.168
